description:
Vincent and his little sister Becca ( a young prodigy) live peacefully under the state ruled by The UNITY and under the watchful eye of the One Nation Protectorate.

Ignorant of the ongoing war with the otherworldly Seraph.

Their tranquillity would not last however as fate has other plans...
name: Episode 1

description: What is this, Operation Bunny Slippers? Chet and Lisa take on a group of gladiator babies and tigers to get the next piece of Nightwear of The Gods. So if you were upset no babies got punched in the face last issue, this one's got you covered!

Ride Captain, Ride!

Well, our down and out Karaoke Hero and Hogo - the bumbing ninja - have managed to find themselves aboard the vessel of Captain Hooker and the Yo-ho-hoes! What is the mysterious job that has been chosen for these two knuckleheads and where has former child actor, Arnold Webster disappeared to?
name: Ride Captain, Ride!

description:
The Last Temptation of Thomas Becker!

The dust has settled and Department REBUS has a new mission for its' recruits. There are signs of someone superpowered in Boston... and it might spell condemnation for EVERYONE!
name: The Last Temptation of Thomas Becker!

description:
Based on Rikki-Tikki-Tavi from Rudyard Kipling's The Jungle Book.

The Chakram clan discover a surprise about the Raksha sanctuary as Rikki prepares to stand alone against Nagaina and her brood in the final battle for control of the bungalow garden.

On Wings of Death

Harry Chen's alter ego, Tai Wu Xia (the Ultimate Kung Fu Warrior) finds himself in more peril, and once again it is at the hands of Fu the Immortal, who wants to see the super fighter dead. This time, Fu sends a flock of Zhenniao, the legendary Chinese bird whose lethal poison brings a most agonizing death to anyone who falls victim. There's no earthly cure for the deadly venom. So, let's see how Tai Wu Xia defends himself and the population of Shanghai, as the birds literally rain down on the city.
name: On Wings of Death

volume.name: Tai Wu Xia - Ultimate Kung Fu Warrior

description: The third collection of the long-running, gay, comic strip, "Troy". Set in a slightly fictional version of West Hollywood, CA, quite possibly the gayest little city in North America, "Troy" follows the lives and loves of Troy, his roommate Rigo, Rigo's on-again, off-again boyfriend Jorge, coupled friends Ray and Derrick, and Troy's hunky, "questioning," boyfriend Nick. In this one, Troy deals with his own insane jealousy, talks to God and gets the big answer, which he promptly forgets, and mixes it up with crazy, naked, ex-gay, "soldiers" for Jesus. Includes "Troy" strips 101 to 150.
name: Jesus Juiced

description:
Following the events of the last issue, Pendragon arrives back in England to find one of his oldest friends has been brutally murdered by his former colleague. Not only that, but his fellow team members - those who haven't been arrested already - are now being hunted by every law enforcement agency in the World.

As well as this, across the globe, a series of coordinated strikes are carried out, reducing the oil supply to western nations to almost zero. How will the British government deliver this news to a populace already on the verge of breakdown? Can our heroes uncover the truth before they are eliminated?

Find out in Vanguard issue 06!

In this third of four chapters in the horror tale of a dusty Kentucky town overrun by killer clowns wantonly slaying abusers of children, young Chelsea Schroeder was lost in the circus freakshow when Stitches and fellow clowns chased away her protectors! Now, rodeo clown Bennie Barona and birthday clown Berniece Roback lead the charge to rescue her from an unspeakable fate!
Raleigh and Lavinia meet up with an antique's collector who is willing to look at their wares. Unfortunately, she is interested in more than just antiques.
name: The Secret of Widow Blume

description: A modern-day Wendy confronts her sanity when she suspects a mysterious flying boy has abducted her little brother. Placed in a new school, Wendy struggles to separate fantasy from reality as those around her start to resemble characters from Neverland.

Zana and Bisa flee their village in search of the city. Zana learns that she's inherited special abilities, her only defense against the perils of the journey, and their destination turns out to be full of fresh danger.

While concert confusion is cleared, romantic feelings are further muddled. News about The Bookstore's imminent closing sends Isabelle into an emotional tailspin. Plus- What's the well guarded secret of Leah's parents?

First blood

Six Cuts, six short stories on 36 pages. Six cuts into a world of Samurai, Monsters and legends of artifical intelligent machines. Six cuts into a picture of violence, dirt and Robots.
name: First Blood

description: Earth's original superheroes return to become Earth's newest superheroes. When humanity faces the threat of annihilation from Devilmon, God's angels come to the rescue. This is an amazing action packed story.
name: Vol. 1

description: An eager youth approaches his audition into Eternity, but in order to indulge the powers that be, he may have to compromise who he is and what he stands for.

The Broken Frontier Anthology unites 50 of the most innovative talents in contemporary comics to share new visions of breaking boundaries and exploring the great unknown. From multiple award winners to the brightest up-and-coming voices, these creators have come together from all over the world to bring you 27 amazing stories about time travel, dystopian deserts, the edges of the universe, human mortality, and much much more!

"The age of words died long ago. Now we settle our differences through action."

Bust is an ongoing post-apocalyptic comic about the downfall of society at the hands of a terrible plague. It is most definitely not about zombies.

"Luckily my fists are mean negotiators."

The Basics of The Apocalypse

Taking place in a post apocalyptic world with a dog mutant named Hannibal and his adopted son/partner, Kid try to find the CSG Foundation who wrote the best and some what magical guide on how to survive the crisis that destroyed the world, hoping that they can assist in rebuilding civilization.
name: The Basics of The Apocalypse

description:
Dreamer's Gate & Rough Stuff

Who do you call when children are disappearing into thin air like magic? Or when your TV is turning the watcher into a mutant abomination? Or when a demon is possessing your computer?

Cthulhu Williams and Co. That's who.

An ex-cop/con with an immunity to monsters, a time traveling amazon from the future, and a stoner grey alien. They'll find a fix for what ails you.
name: Dreamer's Gate & Rough Stuff

description: An alien fights for his life on a prehistoric world, a businessman remembers the true meaning of Halloween and an aging superhero loses his job in just three of the eight stories writer Derek Adnams and a host of today's top indie artists present in this 54 page anthology!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Landing

Hunted, lost, Thy is an exobiologist, member of a scouting mission, who finds herself plunged into an unknown universe.

Fighting for survival - in the middle of a war about to explode and of which she, inadvertently, was the fuse - Thy finds some extravagant allies, aliens with mysterious abilities and needs, with whom she will try to find a way to return to her galaxy of origin.
name: Landing

description:
Ayesha Conway, a little girl who has a fear of monsters, finds out that her mom is a real one. She will either learn to come to terms with this or will further push the monster world away.

Goodnight - Chapter 1

Ayesha, a bright, young girl with a fear of monsters, questions her caring father the whereabouts of her absent mother.
name: Chapter 1

description:
A one-shot comic by Robert James Mediavilla, Diana Naneva and Danny Djeljosevic exploring the frightful vengeance of Nature.

"What is a guardian of the forest without a forest?"

This question has plagued family man Ben Taylor's life since he unwittingly unleashed a supernatural force upon his small town. Now, as the body count rises and the creature draws closer, he and his daughter will come face to face with the brutal answer.
A young boy finds his way amid the ashes of love and the myth of family.

When Daphne and Craig move into a new apartment, they have every reason to believe that they have left their troubled past behind them. Everything seems perfect, but after the discovery of a mysterious hatch in his closet, Craig begins to realize that something disturbingly inhuman is seeking a way into his home, desperate to enter his life in the most intimate and unsettling way possible.

An independent explorer who travels between worlds begins to doubt her transient lifestyle and struggles with the consequences of attachment. The woman outside of time, who can have no permanent residence, a time traveler who realizes the gravity and tyranny of the clock.

The thief wants riches. The knight wants justice. The warrior wants a good battle. The sorcerer wants power. Each adventurer carries a mysterious crystal sphere that will lead to a long-hidden secret beneath the sea.
name: Vol. 1: The Mystery of the Weapons

description: When tragedy befalls an honest hamburger headed cop, an unstoppable sequence of bizarre and barbaric events are set into motion.

Space Brunch is written in episodic adventures, like a cartoon. Each chapter is its own story, from start to finish. The comic has an ongoing continuity within these episodes. As the story goes on, much is revealed about the setting and the characters.

(This first volume collects the first 4 chapters of an ongoing series.)
name: Vol. 1: Space Brunch

description:
Hire Power

The quiet villages of Frankenstein's Europe are about to get a whole lot louder.

When a little girl's father is killed by a monster, she seeks revenge-by hiring an even tougher monster. The two of them face steam-powered robot cops and undead monster gangsters, but when they find the criminal they're hunting, the results are monstrous...

This lightning-paced one-shot from Source Point Press delivers chills and laughs for monster-lovers from age 9 to 999.
name: Hire Power

description:
Eisner Award-nominated writer G. WILLOW WILSON (Air, Superman, Cairo) and superstar artist DAVID LOPEZ (HAWKEYE/MOCKINGBIRD, Catwoman) join forces to bring you the story of two seemingly ordinary orphan girls whose lives are turned upside down by magic. One of them will find herself responsible for saving the world - and the other will become her mortal enemy!

Collects Mystic (2011) #1-4.
name: TPB

description:
NIGHT OF THE FIRE-BEAST is a meta fictional comic book based upon a lost 1958 B movie. It is the first of a series of books based around the titular character - Fire-Beast Dorugan. Rather than consider it a comic book adaptation, the book acts as the actual movie, using exposed wires, stock footage and flimsy sets within the artwork.

1948, a cargo ship sails the Atlantic ocean. Among the crew is Mack, a world weary veteran of the Great War, and Hudson, a young would be adventurer who feels cheated that he was too young to fight in WWII. The ship encounters an unnatural storm and is lost upon a strange island where ancient beasts are unleashed, ready to battle for dominance in a land that shouldn't exist!

The White Flash was a turning point in history.

Nobody quite knows what changed, except for our great brotherhood.

We remember a timeline of a different world because time has been altered.

Time has collapsed on itself.

In this strange world five great nations has risen: Italy, Egypt, America, Great Britain and Japan.

These nations are in one constant and horrendous everlasting war. Not realizing just how frail this universe is.

We are Kronos. We protect what remains of time. We protect the very existence of this reality.

Run, Cowardly Boy

Jakob is a man whose life spirals downward. He is visited by a man who warns him of his nightmares. Little does know that his nightmares will reveal the truth of who he really is.
name: Run, Cowardly Boy

description:
He wanders a futuristic wasteland . A stranger, a lonely door to door peddler. He seems friendly enough, and in passing... He is.

But he's on a mission.

And if The Salesman comes knocking at your door...

You don't... want... to answer

Under Belly presents ...

The Salesmen!

The Escape

Mango and Murphy Magellan - son and father, respectively - are kidnapped from their extraterrestrial home world of Catarrhinia by scientists who seek a rare fruit, the "Ever-Banana". This rare fruit, that abundantly grows on the planet, can be used for fuel, medicine, and food. Mango and Murphy find themselves caught up in a world of trouble as they escape the scientists, find a strange purple alien, a mysterious egg, and flee into the cosmos aboard their newfound, yet trusty cyborg star-turtle, Shelly. The small, but powerful group gathers new friends along the way in their quest to return to Catarrhinia, with hopes of saving their friends and family before ultimate chaos and destruction befalls the place in which they so cherish.
name: The Escape

description:
Survive by Mental Domination

The Church of Illumination was just wiped out by genocide. Now the only members left alive are a suspected serial killer, a corrupt cybernetic cop, an assassin and a mad scientist worth trillions of dollars. Now the only question, revenge or apotheosis.
name: Survive by Mental Domination

description:
To Guide Or Not To Guide?

From successful Kickstarter campaign to Comixology Submit!

In this paranormal parody, two brothers start working as Soul Men, an afterlife organization who guides lost and reluctant souls to Heaven or Hell.
name: To Guide Or Not To Guide?

description: Let a veteran comic book creator help you up your game. SPEED LINES has tips on the comic book craft. The first issue has advice from Wally Wood, where to find great comic book fonts, why you should consider working digitally and the great advice Scott Adams has for cartoonists. This edition also includes exclusive content for writers, pencilers, letterers and inkers not seen in the webcomic.

Two elves are sent to mountainside town of Haromore to investigate the suspicious murders of two dwarvin miners. The culprits are two unlikely suspects, a old woman and a young boy. Wizards, Golems, and Dwarves reveal their true nature in this genre-blending tale combining the best elements detective and fantasy stories.

Travis Lives.

He's watching you.

He's waiting for you.

He's coming for you.

Travis Lives and he won't stop untill you're dead.

Equal parts The Strangers and John Carpenter's Halloween, Suicide Forest is a unique glimpse into the lurking dread that exists within suburbia.

From creators Dave Baker (Action Hospital, Horrible Little People) and Nicole Goux (This Is Not A Girl Gang, Action Hospital), Suicide Forest is a raucous mix of narrative restraint, prowling horror, and brutal violence.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The Tale Before Time Part I : Deep Roots

Kiefer finds himself in the strangest place, with a voice to be his guide. As he uses his military skills Kiefer tries to find his way back home but first he must learn about his family roots starting from the beginning, long before the big bang.
name: Part I : Deep Roots

description: From Lilli Carre, one of the bright new faces in the indy comix scene -- Tales of Woodsman Pete is a collection of vignettes and stories about a solitary albeit gregarious woodsman with a loose grasp on his own personal history and that of the outside world. He forms relationships with his inanimate surroundings and muses to a dead audience, specifically his bear rug, Philippe. His own tales eventually become entangled with that of the legendary Paul Bunyan, and the two become indirectly intertwined, illuminating the discrepancy between the character of the storyteller and the character within his stories. The lives of both Paul and Pete encounter such things as the questionable origin of an ocean and the desire for preservation of everything from a fallen bird to an overused expression that has strayed a stone's throw from its original meaning.
name: GN

description:
The Big Sleep

JUMP into Time Dick with Vivian Gittes and her one true love; the dark, seedy, and gorgeous America of the 1930s. Like so many before her, Gittes is looking for the final big score so she can wash her hands of the dirty work and kick back in the life of, if not luxury, at least glamour and style. All she needs is one. Last. Job.
name: The Big Sleep

description:
In the near future...

...science is able to distill human personalities into a drug-form. Called utopiates -a merging of the words utopia and opiate- these drugs allow users to swap personalities with the "mental imprints" of other people. Every user has their own reasons for seeking chemical escape, but all soon learn the cost of soul swapping is extremely high.

Follow the interconnected lives of four individuals addicted to injecting "souls" in the sci-fi series, UTOPIATES Vol.1, now available from 01 Publishing. At its core, this book is an unflinching portrayal of human behavior at its most extreme.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Origin Story Pt1: Special Edition

Book Info:

Seattle resident Valentina Mobela is not the bravest person in town. But when a hiking trip with her friend leads her to the Lost Tomb of Eris, she'll have to over come her fears and accept her new role as The Valve: Bane of Shadows.

Special Edition includes:

7 pages of never-before-seen concept sketches with commentary

Brightened up pages for better reading
name: Origin Story Pt1: Special Edition

description: LIFE COULDN'T BE MORE COMPLICATED - OR MORE DANGEROUS, FOR ERIC MARTIN. SINCE BECOMING VENGADOR, ERIC WILL COME FACE TO FACE WITH THE CONSEQUENCES OF HIS ACTIONS AND FACE HIS GREATEST VILLIAN, HERROD TO SAVE THE PEOPLE HE LOVES THE MOST. THE QUESTION IS...CAN HE SAVE THEM?
name: Volume 2

description: Top Shelf presents Welcome to Forest Island, the flagship monograph by Bwana Spoons, a painter, designer, screenprinter, zine rocker, and toymaker whose work has been featured on a dizzying array of shoes, skateboards, apparel, baby strollers, art toys, and gallery walls throughout the Americas, Europe, and Asia. All 144 full-color pages - including paintings, maps, sketches, comics, and more - are dedicated to Forest Island: the wild, hyperchromatic paradise Spoons has been constructing with his art for several years. The denizens of this mind-bending island include sweet whale-gators, boozy super-cicadas, arrow-slinging, basket-weaving bearded love tribes, an ex-hobo mushroom farmer, and one brutally intense bat who plays drums in a proto-metal band and would do just about anything to make a bagel relinquish its jelly filling!
name: HC

description: A dinosaur carcass, freshly deceased, is found in the local woods. Meteors fall from the sky. These are strange times... but most people have enough to worry about just getting through the day. Aging couple Flo and Murray face tough news from their doctor, while teen goth Jeanie endures clueless parents and heartless classmates. Their stories -- and more -- twine together into a moving examination of grief, mystery, and human connection. Don't miss Patt Kelley's powerful debut at Top Shelf!
name: GN

volume.name: What Am I Going to Do Without You?
Korak: Suplemento do Mundo de Aventuras

name: Il dramma del travestito per forza
